page.title: 14ECOLOGY WILDLIFE
page.content: {LOCAL WILDLIFE The wildlife in our area contains a wide range of animals, birds, trees, flowers, shrubs and insects. The animals range from worms to foxes including rabbits, hares, rats, mice, moles, stoats, snails, slugs, weasels, hedgehogs and grey squirrels. The birds range from the small wrens to large barn owls and include sparrows, magpies, lapwings, bluetits, cuckoos, robins, great tits, thrushes, song thrushes, swallows, goldfinches, chaffinches, rook, blackbirds,crows, woodpigeons, swifts, house-martins, tawny owls, kestrels and starlings. The insects contain woodlice, house- flies, dragoflies, ants, bees, wasps, butterflies, ladybirds, beetles and earwigs. In the clear streams you see frogs, toads, minnows and trout.
